# gRPC C++ Channel Creation API Documentation

## Overview

The gRPC C++ channel creation APIs enable developers to establish connections to gRPC servers. Channels are the main communication abstraction in gRPC C++, and they encapsulate the underlying socket connections, load balancing, and credential management.

This documentation covers the factory functions for creating channels, the credential system, and channel configuration options.

## Quick Start

### Basic Channel Creation

```cpp
#include <grpcpp/create_channel.h>
#include <grpcpp/security/credentials.h>
#include <grpcpp/client_context.h>

// Create an insecure channel
auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel(
    "localhost:50051",
    grpc::InsecureChannelCredentials()
);

// Create an SSL/TLS channel
auto ssl_channel = grpc::CreateChannel(
    "example.com:443",
    grpc::SslCredentials(grpc::SslCredentialsOptions())
);
```

## Channel Creation Functions

### CreateChannel

**Signature:**
```cpp
std::shared_ptr<Channel> CreateChannel(
    const grpc::string& target,
    const std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials>& creds
);
```

**Description:**
Creates a new `Channel` pointing to a target URI with the specified credentials. This is the primary factory function for most use cases.

**Parameters:**
- `target`: The URI of the endpoint to connect to (e.g., `"localhost:50051"`, `"example.com:443"`).
- `creds`: Credentials to use for the created channel. If the credentials object is null or invalid, a "lame channel" (one on which all operations fail) is returned.

**Returns:**
A `std::shared_ptr<Channel>` that manages the lifetime of the channel object. The shared pointer must not be null, but the channel it points to may be lame.

**Example:**
```cpp
#include <grpcpp/create_channel.h>
#include <grpcpp/security/credentials.h>

int main() {
    std::string target = "localhost:50051";
    auto creds = grpc::InsecureChannelCredentials();
    auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel(target, creds);

    // Use the channel to create stubs and make RPC calls
    return 0;
}
```

---

### CreateCustomChannel

**Signature:**
```cpp
std::shared_ptr<Channel> CreateCustomChannel(
    const grpc::string& target,
    const std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials>& creds,
    const ChannelArguments& args
);
```

**Description:**
Creates a new custom `Channel` with advanced configuration options. This function allows fine-tuning of channel behavior through `ChannelArguments`. It is for advanced use cases and testing only.

**Parameters:**
- `target`: The URI of the endpoint to connect to.
- `creds`: Credentials to use for the created channel.
- `args`: Channel configuration options (see [ChannelArguments](#channelarguments-configuration) section).

**Returns:**
A `std::shared_ptr<Channel>` configured with custom arguments.

**Warning:**
Override default channel arguments only if necessary. Incorrect configuration may result in poor performance or unexpected behavior.

**Example:**
```cpp
#include <grpcpp/create_channel.h>
#include <grpcpp/security/credentials.h>
#include <grpcpp/support/channel_arguments.h>

int main() {
    std::string target = "example.com:443";
    auto creds = grpc::SslCredentials(grpc::SslCredentialsOptions());

    grpc::ChannelArguments args;
    args.SetMaxReceiveMessageSize(10 * 1024 * 1024);  // 10 MB
    args.SetMaxSendMessageSize(10 * 1024 * 1024);
    args.SetLoadBalancingPolicyName("round_robin");

    auto channel = grpc::CreateCustomChannel(target, creds, args);
    return 0;
}
```

---

### CreateCustomChannelWithInterceptors (Experimental)

**Signature:**
```cpp
namespace experimental {
std::shared_ptr<Channel> CreateCustomChannelWithInterceptors(
    const grpc::string& target,
    const std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials>& creds,
    const ChannelArguments& args,
    std::vector<std::unique_ptr<ClientInterceptorFactoryInterface>>
        interceptor_creators
);
}
```

**Description:**
Creates a channel with both custom arguments and client-side interceptors. This is an experimental API that allows per-call interception of RPC operations.

**Parameters:**
- `target`: The URI of the endpoint to connect to.
- `creds`: Credentials to use for the created channel.
- `args`: Channel configuration options.
- `interceptor_creators`: Vector of interceptor factory objects that will be invoked per call.

**Returns:**
A `std::shared_ptr<Channel>` with interceptors attached.

**Note:**
This is an experimental API and may change in future versions.

---

## ChannelCredentials Class

The `ChannelCredentials` class encapsulates authentication credentials for a channel. All credentials used with `CreateChannel` and `CreateCustomChannel` must be passed as `std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials>`.

### Base Class

```cpp
class ChannelCredentials : private grpc::internal::GrpcLibrary {
 public:
  ~ChannelCredentials() override;
  // ... protected and private members
};
```

**Description:**
Abstract base class for all channel credentials. Channel credentials are used to authenticate the client with the server for all calls on a channel. They handle TLS/SSL, mutual authentication, and other channel-level security concerns.

**Reference:**
See [gRPC Authentication Guide](https://grpc.io/docs/guides/auth.html)

---

## Credential Types

### InsecureChannelCredentials

**Signature:**
```cpp
std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials> InsecureChannelCredentials();
```

**Description:**
Creates credentials for unencrypted, unauthenticated channels. Use only for development, testing, and local communication scenarios. Never use in production for sensitive data.

**Example:**
```cpp
#include <grpcpp/security/credentials.h>
#include <grpcpp/create_channel.h>

int main() {
    auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel(
        "localhost:50051",
        grpc::InsecureChannelCredentials()
    );
    return 0;
}
```

---

### SslCredentials

**Signature:**
```cpp
std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials> SslCredentials(
    const SslCredentialsOptions& options
);
```

**Description:**
Creates SSL/TLS credentials with custom certificate and key configuration. This is the standard way to secure gRPC channels in production.

**SslCredentialsOptions Structure:**
```cpp
struct SslCredentialsOptions {
  /// PEM-encoded root certificates for server verification.
  /// If empty, default roots are used.
  grpc::string pem_root_certs;

  /// PEM-encoded client private key (optional).
  /// Can be empty if client authentication is not required.
  grpc::string pem_private_key;

  /// PEM-encoded client certificate chain (optional).
  /// Can be empty if client authentication is not required.
  grpc::string pem_cert_chain;
};
```

**Example:**
```cpp
#include <grpcpp/security/credentials.h>
#include <grpcpp/create_channel.h>
#include <fstream>
#include <sstream>

std::string read_file(const std::string& path) {
    std::ifstream file(path);
    std::stringstream buffer;
    buffer << file.rdbuf();
    return buffer.str();
}

int main() {
    grpc::SslCredentialsOptions opts;

    // Load certificates from files
    opts.pem_root_certs = read_file("ca.crt");
    opts.pem_private_key = read_file("client.key");
    opts.pem_cert_chain = read_file("client.crt");

    auto creds = grpc::SslCredentials(opts);
    auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("example.com:443", creds);

    return 0;
}
```

**Default Root Certificates:**
If `pem_root_certs` is empty, gRPC uses the system's default root certificates. Override this with the `GRPC_DEFAULT_SSL_ROOTS_FILE_PATH` environment variable.

---

### GoogleDefaultCredentials

**Signature:**
```cpp
std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials> GoogleDefaultCredentials();
```

**Description:**
Creates credentials with reasonable defaults for connecting to Google Cloud services. Automatically detects and uses available credentials (Application Default Credentials).

**Warning:**
⚠️ Only use these credentials when connecting to Google endpoints. Using these credentials to connect to other services may allow them to impersonate your client for requests to Google services.

**Example:**
```cpp
#include <grpcpp/security/credentials.h>
#include <grpcpp/create_channel.h>

int main() {
    auto creds = grpc::GoogleDefaultCredentials();
    auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel(
        "pubsub.googleapis.com:443",
        creds
    );
    return 0;
}
```

---

### CompositeChannelCredentials

**Signature:**
```cpp
std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials> CompositeChannelCredentials(
    const std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials>& channel_creds,
    const std::shared_ptr<CallCredentials>& call_creds
);
```

**Description:**
Combines channel credentials with call credentials to create composite credentials. This allows both channel-level (TLS) and call-level (per-RPC) authentication.

**Parameters:**
- `channel_creds`: Base channel credentials (usually TLS credentials).
- `call_creds`: Call credentials (OAuth, service account, etc.) applied to each RPC.

**Example:**
```cpp
#include <grpcpp/security/credentials.h>
#include <grpcpp/create_channel.h>

int main() {
    // Channel-level TLS
    auto ssl_creds = grpc::SslCredentials(grpc::SslCredentialsOptions());

    // Call-level OAuth token
    auto call_creds = grpc::AccessTokenCredentials("oauth_token_here");

    // Combine them
    auto composite = grpc::CompositeChannelCredentials(ssl_creds, call_creds);

    auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("example.com:443", composite);
    return 0;
}
```

---

### XdsCredentials (Experimental)

**Signature:**
```cpp
std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials> XdsCredentials(
    const std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials>& fallback_creds
);
```

**Description:**
Creates XDS (xDS) credentials that fetch security configuration from an xDS control plane. Falls back to provided credentials if xDS is unavailable.

**Parameters:**
- `fallback_creds`: Credentials to use if xDS configuration is unavailable.

---

## ChannelArguments Configuration

The `ChannelArguments` class allows fine-tuning of channel behavior. Use it with `CreateCustomChannel` to customize:
- Message size limits
- Compression
- Load balancing
- SSL/TLS settings
- Resource limits

### Class Definition

```cpp
class ChannelArguments {
 public:
  ChannelArguments();
  ~ChannelArguments();

  ChannelArguments(const ChannelArguments& other);
  ChannelArguments& operator=(ChannelArguments other);
  void Swap(ChannelArguments& other);

  // gRPC-specific setters
  void SetSslTargetNameOverride(const std::string& name);
  void SetCompressionAlgorithm(grpc_compression_algorithm algorithm);
  void SetGrpclbFallbackTimeout(int fallback_timeout);
  void SetSocketMutator(grpc_socket_mutator* mutator);
  void SetUserAgentPrefix(const std::string& user_agent_prefix);
  void SetResourceQuota(const grpc::ResourceQuota& resource_quota);
  void SetMaxReceiveMessageSize(int size);
  void SetMaxSendMessageSize(int size);
  void SetLoadBalancingPolicyName(const std::string& lb_policy_name);
  void SetServiceConfigJSON(const std::string& service_config_json);

  // Generic setters (advanced)
  void SetInt(const std::string& key, int value);
  void SetPointer(const std::string& key, void* value);
  void SetPointerWithVtable(const std::string& key, void* value,
                            const grpc_arg_pointer_vtable* vtable);
  void SetString(const std::string& key, const std::string& value);
};
```

---

### Common Channel Arguments

| Method | Description | Example |
|--------|-------------|---------|
| `SetMaxReceiveMessageSize(int)` | Maximum message size to receive (bytes) | `args.SetMaxReceiveMessageSize(100 * 1024 * 1024);` |
| `SetMaxSendMessageSize(int)` | Maximum message size to send (bytes) | `args.SetMaxSendMessageSize(50 * 1024 * 1024);` |
| `SetLoadBalancingPolicyName(const std::string&)` | LB policy: "round_robin", "pick_first", "ring_hash" | `args.SetLoadBalancingPolicyName("round_robin");` |
| `SetCompressionAlgorithm(grpc_compression_algorithm)` | Compression algorithm (gzip, deflate, etc.) | `args.SetCompressionAlgorithm(GRPC_COMPRESS_GZIP);` |
| `SetSslTargetNameOverride(const std::string&)` | Override SSL hostname for verification | `args.SetSslTargetNameOverride("example.com");` |
| `SetUserAgentPrefix(const std::string&)` | Custom prefix for User-Agent header | `args.SetUserAgentPrefix("MyApp/1.0");` |
| `SetGrpclbFallbackTimeout(int)` | Timeout (ms) before falling back from gRPCLB | `args.SetGrpclbFallbackTimeout(5000);` |
| `SetResourceQuota(const grpc::ResourceQuota&)` | Attach a resource quota to the channel | `args.SetResourceQuota(quota);` |
| `SetServiceConfigJSON(const std::string&)` | Service config in JSON (testing only) | `args.SetServiceConfigJSON("{...}");` |

---

### Generic Argument Setters

For advanced use cases, generic setters allow arbitrary key-value pairs:

```cpp
// Set integer argument
args.SetInt("grpc.max_connection_idle_ms", 30000);

// Set string argument
args.SetString("grpc.http2.min_time_between_pings_ms", "10000");

// Set pointer argument (unowned)
void* my_data = /* ... */;
args.SetPointer("custom_key", my_data);

// Set pointer argument with cleanup (owned)
void* my_data = malloc(sizeof(MyData));
args.SetPointerWithVtable("custom_key", my_data, &my_vtable);
```

---

### ChannelArguments Example

```cpp
#include <grpcpp/create_channel.h>
#include <grpcpp/security/credentials.h>
#include <grpcpp/support/channel_arguments.h>

int main() {
    grpc::ChannelArguments args;

    // Set message size limits (100 MB for both send and receive)
    args.SetMaxReceiveMessageSize(100 * 1024 * 1024);
    args.SetMaxSendMessageSize(100 * 1024 * 1024);

    // Enable compression
    args.SetCompressionAlgorithm(GRPC_COMPRESS_GZIP);

    // Use round-robin load balancing
    args.SetLoadBalancingPolicyName("round_robin");

    // Custom user agent
    args.SetUserAgentPrefix("MyApplication/2.0");

    // Create channel with custom arguments
    auto creds = grpc::SslCredentials(grpc::SslCredentialsOptions());
    auto channel = grpc::CreateCustomChannel(
        "backend.example.com:443",
        creds,
        args
    );

    return 0;
}
```

---

## Call Credentials

Call credentials are applied per-RPC call and can be combined with channel credentials. Common call credential types include:

### ServiceAccountJWTAccessCredentials

```cpp
std::shared_ptr<CallCredentials> ServiceAccountJWTAccessCredentials(
    const grpc::string& json_key,
    long token_lifetime_seconds = kMaxAuthTokenLifetimeSecs  // 3600
);
```

**Description:**
Creates JWT-based call credentials for service account authentication.

**Example:**
```cpp
auto call_creds = grpc::ServiceAccountJWTAccessCredentials(
    R"({"type":"service_account","project_id":"my-project",...})"
);
```

---

### AccessTokenCredentials

```cpp
std::shared_ptr<CallCredentials> AccessTokenCredentials(
    const grpc::string& access_token
);
```

**Description:**
Creates call credentials from an OAuth2 access token fetched out-of-band.

**Warning:**
⚠️ Only use with Google endpoints.

**Example:**
```cpp
auto call_creds = grpc::AccessTokenCredentials("ya29.a0Ad52...");
```

---

### MetadataCredentialsPlugin

```cpp
class MetadataCredentialsPlugin {
 public:
  virtual ~MetadataCredentialsPlugin() {}
  virtual bool IsBlocking() const { return true; }
  virtual const char* GetType() const { return ""; }
  virtual grpc::Status GetMetadata(
      grpc::string_ref service_url,
      grpc::string_ref method_name,
      const grpc::AuthContext& channel_auth_context,
      std::multimap<grpc::string, grpc::string>* metadata) = 0;
  virtual grpc::string DebugString() { return "..."; }
};

std::shared_ptr<CallCredentials> MetadataCredentialsFromPlugin(
    std::unique_ptr<MetadataCredentialsPlugin> plugin
);
```

**Description:**
Custom plugin for adding metadata (headers) to each RPC call.

**Example:**
```cpp
class CustomAuthPlugin : public grpc::MetadataCredentialsPlugin {
 public:
  bool IsBlocking() const override { return true; }

  const char* GetType() const override { return "CustomAuth"; }

  grpc::Status GetMetadata(
      grpc::string_ref service_url,
      grpc::string_ref method_name,
      const grpc::AuthContext& channel_auth_context,
      std::multimap<grpc::string, grpc::string>* metadata) override {
    (*metadata)["authorization"] = "Bearer my_token";
    return grpc::Status::OK;
  }
};

int main() {
    auto plugin = std::make_unique<CustomAuthPlugin>();
    auto call_creds = grpc::MetadataCredentialsFromPlugin(std::move(plugin));

    auto channel_creds = grpc::InsecureChannelCredentials();
    auto composite = grpc::CompositeChannelCredentials(channel_creds, call_creds);

    auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("localhost:50051", composite);
    return 0;
}
```

